# Snyk Maven Vulnerability Remediation

## Purpose

This skill automates the remediation of Snyk-reported dependency vulnerabilities
in Citi CHUB Spring Boot microservices. It reads Snyk findings (Library,
Description, Expected version, Actual version) and applies the correct fix
strategy to `pom.xml` files without modifying Java source code.

## Scope

- Maven `pom.xml` dependency version upgrades via property overrides
- Version property injection in `<properties>` section
- `<dependencyManagement>` overrides when properties are insufficient
- Exclusion of vulnerable transitive dependencies
- Detection and correction of version mismatches (e.g., Boot 4.x deps in Boot 3.x)
- Local build validation (`mvn clean compile`)

### Out of Scope

- Java source code modifications
- Adding new dependencies not already in the dependency tree
- CI/CD pipeline changes
- Snyk policy file (`.snyk`) modifications

