## Remediation Strategy

### Decision Tree

```
Snyk Finding Received
    │
    ├─ Is it a transitive dependency managed by Spring Boot properties?
    │   ├─ YES → STRATEGY 1: Add/update version property in <properties>
    │   └─ NO  → Is the dependency declared directly in pom.xml?
    │       ├─ YES → STRATEGY 3: Update explicit <version> tag
    │       └─ NO  → STRATEGY 2: Add <dependencyManagement> override
    │
    └─ Does version belong to wrong Boot major version?
        └─ YES → STRATEGY 4: Remove explicit version, let BOM manage
```

### Strategy 1: Version Property Override (Primary - 80% of fixes)

The parent BOM respects these standard Spring Boot property names. Adding or
updating them in `<properties>` overrides all matching transitive dependencies.

**Boot 3 (Spring 6) target versions:**

```xml
<properties>
    <!-- Core framework -->
    <spring-framework.version>6.2.19</spring-framework.version>
    <spring-retry.version>2.0.13</spring-retry.version>
    <micrometer.version>1.15.12</micrometer.version>

    <!-- Infrastructure -->
    <netty.version>4.1.135.Final</netty.version>
    <tomcat.version>10.1.55</tomcat.version>

    <!-- Conditional (add only if service uses the library) -->
    <bouncycastle.version>1.84</bouncycastle.version>
    <thymeleaf.version>3.1.4.RELEASE</thymeleaf.version>
    <thymeleaf-spring6.version>3.1.5.RELEASE</thymeleaf-spring6.version>
    <spring-kafka.version>3.3.16</spring-kafka.version>
    <spring-data-commons.version>3.5.12</spring-data-commons.version>
    <neethi.version>3.2.2</neethi.version>
</properties>
```

**Boot 4 (Spring 7) target versions:**

```xml
<properties>
    <!-- Core framework -->
    <spring-framework.version>7.0.8</spring-framework.version>
    <spring-retry.version>2.0.13</spring-retry.version>
    <micrometer.version>1.16.6</micrometer.version>
    <opentelemetry.version>1.62.0</opentelemetry.version>
</properties>
```

### Strategy 2: dependencyManagement Override (Fallback)

Use when `mvn dependency:tree` still shows the old version after applying Strategy 1.

```xml
<dependencyManagement>
    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>{vulnerable.groupId}</groupId>
            <artifactId>{vulnerable.artifactId}</artifactId>
            <version>{expected.version}</version>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>
</dependencyManagement>
```

### Strategy 3: Direct Version Update

For dependencies with explicit `<version>` in `<dependencies>`:

```xml
<!-- Before -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>commons-io</groupId>
    <artifactId>commons-io</artifactId>
    <version>2.11.0</version>  <!-- Vulnerable -->
</dependency>

<!-- After -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>commons-io</groupId>
    <artifactId>commons-io</artifactId>
    <version>2.22.0</version>  <!-- Fixed -->
</dependency>
```

### Strategy 4: Remove Version Mismatch

**Rule:** For `org.springframework.boot` or `org.springframework.cloud` artifacts,
NEVER hardcode a version. Let the parent BOM manage it.

```xml
<!-- BAD: Boot 4.x dep in a Boot 3.x project -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test</artifactId>
    <version>4.0.6</version>
    <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>

<!-- FIXED: Remove version, inherit from parent BOM -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test</artifactId>
    <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>
```

**Exceptions** (these DO need explicit versions — not in parent BOM):
- `cmr-em-microserviceframework` (Citi internal)
- `javapasswordsdk` (CyberArk)
- `springdoc-openapi-ui`
- `hsqldb`, `ojdbc8` (specific classifier/version)
- `commons-collections4`, `commons-io`, `org.json:json`
- `solace-jms-spring-boot-starter`
- `kafka-clients` (when pinned separately from spring-kafka)

