## Maintenance

When new Snyk findings arrive:

1. Check if a newer `ccp-spring-boot-starter-parent-master` is available on Nexus.
   If yes, update the parent version first — this is the cleanest fix.
2. Look up the vulnerable library in the CVE-to-Property Mapping table.
3. If not listed, determine if the library is transitive (use `mvn dependency:tree`)
   and find the appropriate Spring Boot property name from
   [Spring Boot Dependency Versions](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/appendix/dependency-versions/properties.html).
4. Add the new property/version to this SKILL file.
5. Validate with `mvn clean compile -DskipTests` and `mvn dependency:tree`.

