## Build and Test Procedure (Local)

### Prerequisites

- JDK 21 installed and `JAVA_HOME` set
- Maven 3.9+ installed
- Access to Citi Nexus repository (for parent BOM and internal dependencies)
- `settings.xml` configured with Nexus mirror and credentials

### Commands

```cmd
REM Navigate to the microservice project root (where pom.xml lives)
cd <service-project-root>

REM 1. Clean build (skip tests for quick validation)
mvn clean compile -DskipTests

REM 2. Full build with tests
mvn clean verify

REM 3. Package the WAR
mvn clean package -DskipTests

REM 4. Check effective POM (useful to verify property resolution)
mvn help:effective-pom -Doutput=effective-pom.xml

REM 5. Full dependency tree (save to file for review)
mvn dependency:tree -DoutputFile=dependency-tree.txt

REM 6. Check for specific library version
mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=org.springframework:spring-core
```

### Troubleshooting Build Failures

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `Could not resolve dependencies` | Parent BOM version not in local cache | Run `mvn dependency:resolve` or check Nexus access |
| `NoClassDefFoundError` in tests | Boot version mismatch (4.x dep in 3.x) | Remove explicit version on spring-boot artifacts |
| `package does not exist` | Major version API change | Check if the import moved (javax → jakarta, etc.) |
| `Plugin not found` | `ert-maven-plugin` is Citi-internal | Ensure settings.xml has Citi Nexus plugin repository |

